709356f-a.title: Manhattan: 6th Avenue - 12th Street (West)
709356f-a.text:
Sixth Avenue, north from West 12th Street, showing demolition
of the old '1'' line. At the left are low buildings that extend
across 13th to 14th Streets. On the right is the 10-story utili-
tarian structure occupying the 13th to 14th Street frontage and
which was formerly the business establishment of R. H. Macy, de-
partment store retailer.
To the left is the toweri.g Empire State Building.
February 119, 1939
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIOHS

711136f-a.title: Manhattan: 12th Street (West) - 6th Avenue
711136f-a.text:
119-125 West 12th Street, north side, west of Sixth Ave., showing the
First Reformed Presbyterian Church. In 1907, this structure became known
as the Second United Presbyterian Church which was demolished in 1918.
Upon this site was erected a 6-story apartment building which stands today
11938).
About 1910.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
